cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO. 

The paper focuses on developing a fast and efficient visual tracking algorithm using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the network structure and training data, which suggests it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of CNNs for tracking also implies it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper evaluates the proposed algorithm on two benchmarks, which suggests it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of the algorithm for real-time tracking suggests it could belong to cs.RO (Robotics).
